# Project Context

## Overview
This project is a professional portfolio built with a modern tech stack focusing on performance, type safety, and visual appeal.

## Technologies
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript (Strict mode)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui (Radix UI primitives)
- **Database**: Drizzle ORM with libSQL (Turso in production, SQLite locally)
- **Environment**: @t3-oss/env-nextjs + Zod for validated environment variables
- **Visuals**: React Three Fiber (R3F) + Three.js for animated 3D backgrounds

## Principles & Best Practices
- **Server First**: Use Server Components by default. Use `"use client"` only when necessary (interactivity, browser APIs, R3F).
- **Type Safety**: Strict TypeScript throughout. Domain types are centralized in `src/lib/types/`.
- **Configuration**: Environment variables are validated via a schema and accessed through a central config in `src/lib/config/`.
- **Database Access**: All runtime database reads go through `src/lib/db/queries.ts` to maintain a clean separation between schema and data access.
- **Styling**: Use the `cn()` utility for conditional class merging.

## Architecture
- `src/app/`: Routing and page layout.
- `src/components/`: Feature-based component organization.
- `src/lib/`: Shared logic, database configuration, and types.
- `src/lib/db/seed/data/`: Initial data source for the project.
